div.span: Turbulent Architects are Introverted, Intuitive, Thinking, Judging and Turbulent. Architects are imaginative and strategic thinkers, with a plan for everything. These thoughtful tacticians love perfecting the details of life, applying creativity and rationality.
Likely prefers fewer, yet deep and meaningful, social interactions and feels drawn to calmer environments.
Likely very imaginative and open-minded, focusing on hidden meanings and distant possibilities.
Likely focuses on objectivity and rationality, putting effectiveness above social harmony.
Likely decisive, thorough, and highly organized. Values clarity and prefers planning to spontaneity.
Likely self-conscious, sensitive to stress, success-driven, perfectionistic, and eager to improve.
